[
    {
        "content": "<p>Consider the 1-category where the objects are categories and the morphisms are cofunctors, aka <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/retrofunctor\">[[retrofunctor]]</a> s. Does this category have products or pullbacks? If so, what are they?</p>",
        "id": 464957135,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathaniel Virgo",
        "timestamp": 1724570642
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, the 1-category of categories and retrofunctors has all limits. This is Corollary 8.78 in <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2312.00990\">Polynomial Functors: A Mathematical Theory of Interaction</a>.</p>",
        "id": 464959307,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Clarke",
        "timestamp": 1724572508
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I thought I remembered the book having an explicit description of products, but I couldn't find it, so perhaps it was only in a previous version.</p>",
        "id": 464959352,
        "sender_full_name": "Bryce Clarke",
        "timestamp": 1724572559
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks! The proof there is rather indirect, so I still have the question of what they are explicitly.</p>",
        "id": 464963315,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathaniel Virgo",
        "timestamp": 1724574054
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is this the category of polynomial comonads on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{Set}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">Set</span></span></span></span></span>, in other words the category of comonoids wrt polynomial composition? </p>\n<p>If so, then let <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi><mo>:</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">y</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">t</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">♯</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G: \\mathsf{Poly} \\to \\mathsf{Cat}^{\\sharp}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">Poly</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9334em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">Cat</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.9334em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1473em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">♯</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> be the right adjoint to the forgetful functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>U</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span></span></span></span>, which is comonadic. <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> preserves products, so that a product <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∏</mo><mi>i</mi></msub><mi>G</mi><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\prod_i GP_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0497em;vertical-align:-0.2997em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol small-op\" style=\"position:relative;top:0em;\">∏</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.162em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2997em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> of cofree comonoids <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">GP_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> can be formed as <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mo>∏</mo><mi>i</mi></msub><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G(\\prod_i P_i)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0497em;vertical-align:-0.2997em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol small-op\" style=\"position:relative;top:0em;\">∏</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.162em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2997em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.1389em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>. </p>\n<p>Meanwhile, by comonadicity, a general comonoid <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> is canonically represented as an equalizer of maps between cofree comonoids (formed at the level of underlying polynomial functors): </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><mrow><mi>η</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></mover></mo><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><mi>C</mi><mi><mover><mo><mo><munder><mo><mo>⇉</mo></mo><mrow><mi>η</mi><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></munder></mo></mo><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><mi>η</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></mover></mi><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C \\overset{\\eta C}{\\to} GUC \\overset{GU\\eta C}{\\underset{\\eta GUC}{\\rightrightarrows}} GUGUC</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1923em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.1923em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.614em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">η</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.5617em;vertical-align:-1.0612em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.5004em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.675em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.1749em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">η</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">G</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop amsrm\">⇉</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.0612em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.9221em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">G</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">η</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.0612em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> </p>\n<p>where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>η</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\eta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">η</span></span></span></span> is the unit of the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>U</mi><mo>⊣</mo><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">U \\dashv G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⊣</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> adjunction. Given a family of comonoids <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, their product is the equalizer of </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∏</mo><mi>i</mi></msub><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mi><mover><mo><mo><munder><mo><mo>⇉</mo></mo><mrow><msub><mo>∏</mo><mi>i</mi></msub><mi>η</mi><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow></munder></mo></mo><mrow><msub><mo>∏</mo><mi>i</mi></msub><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><mi>η</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow></mover></mi><msub><mo>∏</mo><mi>i</mi></msub><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><mi>G</mi><mi>U</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\prod_i GUC_i \\overset{\\prod_i GU\\eta C_i}{\\underset{\\prod_i\\eta GUC_i}{\\rightrightarrows}} \\prod_i GUGUC_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.8328em;vertical-align:-1.1968em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol small-op\" style=\"position:relative;top:0em;\">∏</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.162em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2997em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><s